      • setId

        public void setId(Id id)
        sets the id of the object. If the object is new then this parameter will be ignored and a new id will be generated. Use setNewId to set the id of a new object.

      • getNewId

      • setNewId

        public void setNewId(Id newId)
        if create an identifiable object with a specific id, then this is what you set. The id generator won't create a new id but will use this field as the id
        Parameters:
        newId -
